The paper focuses on semantic segmentation using fully convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The application of the method is for brain tumor segmentation, which falls under the category of medical image analysis and could also be classified as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes modifications to the network architecture and loss function, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using metrics such as precision and recall, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
